article.description: Jeff Short had 28 points and seven rebounds, leading Norfolk State to a 71-65 win over Division II Mercy (NY) Wednesday night.
article.headline: Short scores 28, Norfolk State tops D-II Mercy (NY) 71-65
article.linkText: Short scores 28, Norfolk State tops D-II Mercy (NY) 71-65
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Jeff Short had 28 points and seven rebounds, leading Norfolk State to a 71-65 win over Division II Mercy (N.Y,) Wednesday night. Short was 10 of 12 from the field and 2 of 2 from 3-point range in a rare home game for Norfolk State (3-4), which plays 13 of its first 15 games on the road. William Robinson's layup with 2:01 remaining for Mercy drew the Mavericks to 65-60, but baskets from Zaynah Robinson and Preston Bungei put the Spartans up by nine with 1:04 to play. Mercy shot just 33 percent from the field, and its starting lineup combined to miss 39 of 58 shots. Shaquille Stokes was 7 of 20 for 20 points, and Tyseem Lyles had 13 points on 4-of-12 shooting to go with six rebounds. --- This story has been corrected to change nickname in 3rd paragraph.
